metadata.name: #0_FirstContact
metadata.description:
The arrogant evolution of mankind has brought in visitors from the outside.
They laid waste to the civilizations that had been built up over the ages, as if in mockery.
The towers that looked up to the heavens and the cardiac that burned with heat all became equally meaningless.

However, only the light of the "meteors" twinkled with phosphorescence, unchanging.
